AGI - "It is urgent to alarm Europe >". The President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen, declared this at the end of the London summit on Ukraine. The message it sends to the United States is "we are ready to stand by your side to defend democracy, to defend the rule of law," he added.
&nbsp;
"We cannot invade our neighbors, attack them. We can't change the boundaries with force. And it is in our common interest to avoid wars in the future. These rules are important. We need to be clear about this. And together our democracies will fight for this principle," he said.&nbsp;
<h2> 6 March plan for rehabilitation
"We must urgently rearma Europe. And for this reason we will present a complete plan for the rearmament of Europe on March 6, when we will have our European Council of Leaders." The President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen, declared this at the end of the London summit on Ukraine.
&nbsp;
"One thing is certain: we must increase the defence, we must absolutely increase the defence spending and for this reason we need a clear plan in the European Union by the Member States and the common areas of Europe, such as the defence of the European airspace, but we also need more budgetary space for defence," he added.&nbsp;
We must put Ukraine in a strong position, which has the means to protect itself. From economic survival to military resilience." He declared the President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen.

